sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer
    participant S as Sales Team [R:Accountable]
    participant CO as Compliance Officer [R:Responsible]
    participant F as Finance [R:Responsible]
    participant FD as Finance Director [R:Accountable]
    participant IT as IT Ops [R:Responsible]
    participant AU as Audit Log [R:Informed]

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - RACI labels added to all participants
    C->>S: Submit onboarding request
    Note over S: 📋 DOC GATE 1: Validate request completeness<br/>(Required: Company docs, contact info, tax ID)
    S->>AU: Log request received (SOX-CTL-001)
    %% END CHANGED SECTION

    S->>F: Credit check request

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Pre-approval compliance checkpoint
    F->>F: Risk Assessment (Score >750, Verified Company, Clean Payment History)
    F->>CO: Submit risk assessment for compliance review
    CO->>CO: SOX Control Check (SOX-CTL-002)<br/>Segregation of Duties validation
    CO->>AU: Log compliance review outcome
    Note over CO: 📋 DOC GATE 2: Risk assessment documentation<br/>(Required: Credit report, risk score, compliance sign-off)
    CO-->>F: Compliance clearance granted
    %% END CHANGED SECTION

    alt Low-Risk: Score >750 AND Verified AND No Payment Issues
        F-->>S: Auto-Approved (Expedited Path)
        %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - SOX control for auto-approval audit trail
        F->>AU: Log auto-approval decision (SOX-CTL-003)
        Note over F: 📋 DOC GATE 3: Auto-approval evidence package<br/>(Required: Risk score, compliance clearance, approval timestamp)
        %% END CHANGED SECTION
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (immediate)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials (within 24h)
    else High-Risk: Fails any risk criteria
        F->>FD: Escalate for Finance Director approval
        %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - SOX control for manual approval with documentation gate
        FD->>CO: Request independent compliance assessment (SOX-CTL-004)
        CO-->>FD: Compliance risk opinion delivered
        Note over FD: 📋 DOC GATE 4: Manual approval evidence package<br/>(Required: FD justification memo, compliance opinion,<br/>risk mitigation plan)
        FD->>AU: Log manual approval decision with justification (SOX-CTL-005)
        %% END CHANGED SECTION
        FD-->>F: Approval decision (24h SLA)
        F-->>S: Approval relayed
        S->>IT: Provision accounts
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
    end

    C->>IT: First login confirmation

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Post-onboarding compliance checkpoint and final documentation gate
    IT->>CO: Onboarding completion compliance verification (SOX-CTL-006)
    CO->>CO: Verify all documentation gates satisfied
    CO->>AU: Log final compliance attestation
    Note over CO,AU: 📋 DOC GATE 5: Onboarding closure package<br/>(Required: All prior gate artifacts, access provisioning<br/>evidence, compliance attestation, RACI sign-off sheet)
    CO-->>IT: Compliance verification confirmed
    %% END CHANGED SECTION

    IT->>S: Onboarding complete [C:Consulted]
    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - RACI Matrix Reference
    Note over C,AU: RACI Summary:<br/>Sales [A] - Accountable for end-to-end onboarding<br/>Finance [R] - Responsible for credit/risk assessment<br/>Finance Director [A] - Accountable for high-risk approvals<br/>Compliance Officer [R] - Responsible for SOX controls<br/>IT Ops [R] - Responsible for provisioning<br/>Customer [I] - Informed at key milestones<br/>Audit Log [I] - Informed at all control points
    %% END CHANGED SECTION

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Added a Compliance Officer participant and an Audit Log participant to enforce segregation of duties and maintain a SOX-compliant audit trail. Inserted six SOX control points (SOX-CTL-001 through SOX-CTL-006) at critical process stages: request intake, pre-approval compliance review, auto-approval logging, manual escalation independent assessment, manual approval justification logging, and post-onboarding compliance attestation. Added five documentation gates requiring specific artifact packages before the process can proceed past each checkpoint. Labeled all participants with RACI designations and included a summary RACI matrix note for audit reference.